Paragraph description:
Café Momentum connects interns to community resources and services that help meet their basic needs and establish a baseline of stability in their lives. 

Resource and referral categories include housing, food assistance, health care, child care, government-issued or state identification, legal aid, substance abuse support, etc. This strategy also includes resource navigation education, critical document support, and providing interns with donated essential and personal care items.
Output:
Referrals provided by category (number of)
IDs obtained by youth (number of)
Immediate Outcomes <1year:
Increased access to health care services
Increased access to basic needs
Intermediate Outcomes 1-5 years: Increased ability to navigate and use services
Long-term Outcomes (5-10+ years):
Improved social-emotional well-being 
Increased sense of agency
Increased education attainment 
Increased job stability 
Decreased justice system involvement

Strategy: Mental health and trauma recovery support
Paragraph description: Café Momentum provides mental health and healing support to their interns through mental health meetings and service planning, as well as individual and group therapy sessions. To provide holistic and trauma-informed care, each intern also participates in a Adverse Childhood Experiences (ACEs) screening and a behavioral and emotional screening.
Output:
Mental health service plans (number of) 
Individual therapy sessions (number of)
Group therapy sessions (number of)  
Behavioral screenings (number of) 
Interns with ACE screenings (percent of)
ACEs score (average)
Restorative circles (number of)
Immediate Outcomes <1year:
Improved social-emotional skills
Improved self-esteem and self-efficacy 
Improved conflict management skills
Intermediate Outcomes 1-5 years:
Increase in healthy relationships 
High school graduation or GED attainment
Increased credential attainment

Paragraph description:
Café Momentum supports life skills and personal development by providing interns with education on workplace skill development, sexual health and healthy relationships, online and social media etiquette, rights and systems navigation, and financial literacy. Café Momentum also coordinates enrichment activities for youth (e.g., attending a musical, visiting a museum, etc.). 

Interns receive one-on-one support from a case manager to set personal goals and help monitor their completion of Café Momentum’s Tiers of Success.Through family visits, Café Momentum connects and promotes program awareness among interns’ family members. During this visit, case managers may also gain insights on intern and family needs.
Output:
Case management (hours of)
Enrichment activities (number of)
Tiers of Success completed (number of)
Wages earned on key learning activities (average)
Immediate Outcomes <1year:
Improved social-emotional skills
Improved self-esteem and self-efficacy
Increased sense of belonging
Expand professional network 
Increased employability
Intermediate Outcomes 1-5 years:
Increase in healthy relationships
Increased social capital
Increased credential attainment 
Increased employment

Paragraph description: To participate in the program, Café Momentum interns must be enrolled in high school or the GED equivalent.  Café Momentum supports academic progress by providing interns with education planning services, enrollment assistance, attendance tracking, tutoring, and post-secondary prep (e.g., test prep, college application support, scholarship and FAFSA support, interview prep, college tours, etc.)
Output:
Interns enrolled in high school or GED program (percentage of)
Interns making academic progress (number of)
Immediate Outcomes <1year:
Increased academic engagement 
Increased access to educational opportunities
Intermediate Outcomes 1-5 years:
High school graduation or GED attainment
Increased credential attainment 
Decrease in chronic absenteeism

Paragraph description: Café Momentum’s program requires each intern to be employed and trained in every aspect of operating a fine dining restaurant–cooking, serving, bussing, etc. From this training, interns earn Cafe Momentum restaurant skills certifications and industry-recognized certifications (e.g., ServSafe Food Handlers).
Output:
ServSafe certifications (number of)
Station certifications earned (number of)
Full certifications earned (number of)
Paid hours (number of) 
Wages earned on shift at Restaurant (average) 
Wages earned on key learning activities (average)
Immediate Outcomes <1year:
Improved self-esteem and self-efficacy
Improved interpersonal skills 
Increased employability

Paragraph description: Café Momentum promotes job attainment through career exploration activities such as informational interviews, job shadows, externships, etc. Interns also participate in job search workshops (e.g., resume drafting, interview training, professional communications, etc.) and receive one-on-one coaching. Café Momentum also coordinates professional networking opportunities for interns (e.g., guest speakers, tours, etc.)
Output:
Externships completed (number of) 
Job shadows completed (number of) 
Informational interviews (number of) 
Jobs attained (number of) 
Starting wage (average) 
Professional connections (number of)
Immediate Outcomes <1year:
Expand professional network 
Improved interpersonal skills 
Improved self-esteem and self-efficacy
Intermediate Outcomes 1-5 years:
Increased social capital
Increased credential attainment 
Increased employment

Paragraph description: Café Momentum provides all interns with violence prevention education, transportation planning, and de-escalation and conflict mediation.
Output:
Workshops attended (number of) 
De-escalation incidents (number of) 
Behavioral agreements/safety plans (number of)
Immediate Outcomes <1year:
Improved conflict management skills 
Improved interpersonal skills 
Sense of safety at Café Momentum
Intermediate Outcomes 1-5 years:
Increase in healthy relationships 
Avoid justice system involvement

Paragraph description: Café Momentum assists interns with exiting the justice system. Activities include coordinating and monitoring community service or “Give Back Hours,” court and trial support, and staff relationship-building with probation officers. Café Momentum also provides transition planning and one-on-one case management support to ensure interns are meeting probation requirements.
Output:
Youth in compliance with probation (percentage of)
Youth in alignment with restitution (number of)
Community service hours completed (number of) 
Staff court appearances (number of) 
Staff-probation officer relationships (number of)
Immediate Outcomes <1year:
Improved self-esteem and self-efficacy 
Increased progress towards justice system exit

Paragraph description: Café Momentum maintains and strengthens connections with interns by providing post-internship planning and outreach and follow-up after program exit. Interns may continue to benefit from the program after exit by receiving referrals and job search assistance, and by attending community-building activities and events.
Output:
Interns exiting program (number of)
Interns enrolled in education program at exit (number of)
Interns employed at exit (number of)
Post-internship engagements (number of)
Referrals provided (number of)
Community-building activities and events (number of)
Immediate Outcomes <1year:
Expand professional network 
Increased sense of belonging
Increased access to basic needs
Intermediate Outcomes 1-5 years:
Increased social capital
Increased employment
Increased credential attainment
